TI  - Ethical preferences for influencing superiors: A 41-society study
JO  - Journal of International Business Studies
SP  - 1022
EP  - 1045
VL  - 40
IS  - 6
AB  - With a 41-society sample of 9990 managers and professionals, we used hierarchical linear modeling to investigate the impact of both macro-level and micro-level predictors on subordinate influence ethics. While we found that both macro-level and micro-level predictors contributed to the model definition, we also found global agreement for a subordinate influence ethics hierarchy. Thus our findings provide evidence that developing a global model of subordinate ethics is possible, and should be based upon multiple criteria and multilevel variables.
